714459f-a.title: Manhattan: 75th Street (West) - Columbus Avenue
714459f-a.text:
46 West 75th Street, south side, west of Columbis Avenue.
Vbout 1911.

714458f-a.title: Manhattan: 75th Street (West) - Columbus Avenue
714458f-a.text:
West 75th Street, east from (about. No. 36 on right) a point east of Columbus Ave., to Central Park West. At the latter point are the Kenilworth and the Hotel San Remo occupying the N.W. and S.W. corners
respectively.
September 29, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

714460f-a.title: Manhattan: 75th Street (West) - Columbus Avenue
714460f-a.text:
West 75th Street, west from (No. 50 on left) a point east of Columbus Ave. (Sixth and Ninth Aves. Elevated Line thereon), to the North (Hudson) River. The five private dwellings on the left are Nos. 50 to 58. At the corner is a 6-story apartment house, No. 60 (also 313-315 Columbus Ave.). Opposite the latter is the 7-story Del Monte, 100-102 (also 306-316 Columbus Ave.) another apartment house located at the S.W. corner of
Columbus Ave.
September 29, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
